    <segment id="1" parent="30" relname="solutionhood">John BAILAR asks &quot;What are we really trying to accomplish in the long run?&quot;</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="17" relname="span">
Let me tell you about my goal in one particular STS project</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="background"> (in collaboration
with Mary Cawte).</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="18" relname="span"> Of course other people will have different goals,</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="2" relname="elaboration"> as I do
myself in other projects.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="25" relname="span">

The ultimate goal is a world without war, in which conflicts are waged using
only nonviolent methods.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="20" relname="span"> A step towards this is to help promote the use of
nonviolent methods of struggle,</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="23" relname="span"> such as strikes, boycotts and noncooperation,
as an alternative to military defence.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="22" relname="span"> There is a considerable historical
experience and literature on this alternative,</segment>
    <segment id="21" parent="9" relname="concession"> though it is not widely known.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="11" relname="antithesis">

Currently a large portion of R&amp;D is directly or indirectly related to
military goals.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="24" relname="span"> Our project is to see how science and technology can be used
instead to make nonviolent struggle more effective.</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="11" relname="elaboration"> We have searched many
literatures, interviewed scientists and engineers, given talks, and published
queries and accounts in magazines and electronic lists to stimulate
responses.</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="26" relname="summary"> The project itself is part of the process of creating awareness of
nonviolent alternatives to military systems.</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="15" relname="concession">

One doesn&apos;t have to be an STS specialist to carry out this research,</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="28" relname="span"> but it&apos;s
as good a location as any.</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="29" relname="span"> For those who are interested in our topic,</segment>
    <segment id="27" parent="16" relname="enablement"> I would
be happy to provide copies of articles.</segment>
